headline.print_headline: Spain's Repsol Accepts $5B for Argentine Unit
headline.main: Spain's Repsol Accepts $5B for Argentine Unit

lead_paragraph: Spain's Repsol energy firm says its board has accepted a $5 billion (3.6 billion euro) offer from Argentina as compensation for the South American country's seizure of the company's YPF petroleum division.
